#BurroNation We're working everyday to make sure we are ready to deliver a quality education when we come back.

Thank you to everyone for respecting the facility closure. We have many daycare children of our emergency personnel parents still needing service and we want to keep them and our amazing daycare staff safe every day.

The kitchen and office staff have worked to organize lunch preparation for students beginning Wednesday. You should have received an email tonight letting you know lunches are free for those that request them.

Please continue to check your email for more information regarding lunches and other updates each day.

post_text:
Last night the girls basketball team hosted the Chieftains from Klawock, Alaska! Klawock is located on an island in SE Alaska and is a three hour ferry ride from the nearest "big" town. After the game we ate together, traded stories, and learned about life from a different perspective. Thanks to the Chieftain players and coaches for this great opportunity!

Learn more about their trip and see more photos at Winona Daily News: https://www.winonadailynews.com/sports/local/photos-alaska-girls-basketball-team-visits-bluff-country/collection_0e64fdd3-bd39-587d-b9ce-4d7785b400e0.html#1

post_text:
Thank you again to our local farmers and the Bayer Fund. The $25,000 grant will be used to outfit our new Creator Space classroom with 3D printers, touch screen LED monitors, robotics equipment, air tools and furniture.

America’s Farmers Grow Rural Education works with farmers to nominate rural public school districts to compete for STEM grants. These grants support math and science education by funding projects like technology upgrades,
greenhouses and laboratory equipment. More information about the program can be found at www.AmericasFarmers.com

post_text: Thank you to our local farmers for nominating Lanesboro Schools to submit a grant proposal to @AmericasFarmers Grow Rural Education. We were awarded a $25,000 grant and will be using those dollars to purchase 3D Printers, Robotics Supplies, and other hands-on equipment for the new Creator Space classroom. Great news!
